TITLE: Creating a Comment in RedwoodJS Service (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Adds a typed `createComment` function to 'api/src/services/comments/comments.ts'. It defines an interface `CreateCommentArgs` specifying the `input` parameter should conform to `Prisma.CommentCreateInput`. It uses `db.comment.create({ data: input })` for database insertion.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/tutorial/chapter6/comments-schema.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
```javascript title="api/src/services/comments/comments.ts"
interface CreateCommentArgs {
  input: Prisma.CommentCreateInput
}

export const createComment = ({ input }: CreateCommentArgs) => {
  return db.comment.create({
    data: input,
  })
}
