TITLE: Configuring Redwood API Server with Fastify Plugins
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet demonstrates using the `configureApiServer` option within `createServer`. This async function receives the Fastify server instance, allowing registration and configuration of Fastify plugins (like `@fastify/compress` and `@fastify/rate-limit`) before Redwood's core API plugin is registered, ensuring proper encapsulation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/server-file.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const server = await createServer({
  logger,
  async configureApiServer(server) {
    await server.register(import('@fastify/compress'), {
      global: true,
      threshold: 1024,
      encodings: ['deflate', 'gzip'],
    })

    await server.register(import('@fastify/rate-limit'), {
      max: 100,
      timeWindow: '5 minutes',
    })
  },
})
