TITLE: Fetching User Roles from Database in RedwoodJS getCurrentUser (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows an alternative `getCurrentUser` implementation in `api/lib/auth.js` that retrieves roles from a database instead of the JWT. It uses Prisma Client (`db`) to query the `UserRole` table, filtering by the user's `uuid` (found in the decoded JWT's `sub` claim). The fetched role names are then mapped into an array and added to the returned `currentUser` object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/04_how-to/role-based-access-control.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export const getCurrentUser = async (decoded) => {
  const userRoles = await db.userRole.findMany({
    where: { user: { uuid: decoded.sub } },
    select: { name: true },
  })

  const roles = userRoles.map((role) => {
    return role.name
  })

  return context.currentUser || { roles }
}
```

