TITLE: Testing a Divide Function for Successful Division - React/JSX/TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a unit test written in TypeScript using RedwoodJS's testing utilities to validate the correct behavior of a 'divide' serverless function. It mocks an HTTP event with dividend and divisor, invokes the handler, and checks for a successful division result (status 200 and correct quotient). Dependencies include '@redwoodjs/testing/api' for mock event creation, and the 'divide' function handler.
