TITLE: Customizing the Default Error Message in RedwoodJS GraphQL Handler - TypeScript/TSX
DESCRIPTION: This TSX snippet shows how to set a custom default error message using the defaultError property in createGraphQLHandler. If an unhandled error occurs, the specified string (e.g., 'Sorry about that') is sent in the response instead of the error detail. Other properties initialize logging, directives, and services. The onException callback allows custom handling such as disconnecting from the database. Requires RedwoodJS server libraries and relevant GraphQL handler dependencies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/graphql.md#_snippet_78

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const handler = createGraphQLHandler({
  loggerConfig: { logger, options: {} },
  directives,
  sdls,
  services,
  defaultError: 'Sorry about that', // \uD83D\uDC49 Customize the error message
  onException: () => {
    // Disconnect from your database with an unhandled exception.
    db.$disconnect()
  },
})
```

