TITLE: Granting Public Access to Single and Multiple Post Queries in RedwoodJS (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript GraphQL schema snippet enables public (unauthenticated) access to both 'posts' and single 'post' queries using the @skipAuth directive. All mutations continue to require authentication via @requireAuth. This approach is useful for exposing post data to public-facing pages while keeping data modification protected. Place this in the RedwoodJS API codebase, ensuring any sensitive logic is handled on the backend.
