TITLE: Defining a Custom React Hook useAccumulator in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code defines a custom React hook named `useAccumulator`. It utilizes the `useState` hook to maintain an accumulator state (`total`), initialized with `initialValue`. It returns an object containing the current `total` and an `add` function to increment the total.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/testing.md#_snippet_33

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
```js title="web/src/hooks/useAccumulator/useAccumulator.js"
const useAccumulator = (initialValue) => {
  const [total, setTotal] = useState(initialValue)

  const add = (value) => {
    const newTotal = total + value
    setTotal(newTotal)
    return newTotal
  }

  return { total, add }
}
```
