TITLE: Building a Custom Required Field Component (RedwoodJS, JSX)
DESCRIPTION: Implements a composite custom input field component in RedwoodJS, integrating react-hook-form registration and Redwood's error styling utilities. The RequiredField component provides internal label rendering, input binding, error display via <FieldError>, and automatic required validation. It requires '@redwoodjs/forms' package, and is meant for complex domain-specific fields within custom forms.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/forms.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { FieldError, useErrorStyles, useRegister } from '@redwoodjs/forms'

const RequiredField = ({ label, name, validation }) => {
  const register = useRegister({
    name,
    validation: {...validation, required: true}
  })

  const { className: labelClassName, style: labelStyle } = useErrorStyles({
    className: `my-label-class`,
    errorClassName: `my-label-error-class`,
    name,
  })

  const { className: inputClassName, style: inputStyle } = useErrorStyles({
    className: `my-input-class`,
    errorClassName: `my-input-error-class`,
    name,
  })

  return (
    <>
      <label className={labelClassName} style={labelStyle}>{label}</label>
      <input
        className={inputClassName}
        style={inputStyle}
        type="text"
        {...register}
      />
      <FieldError name={name}>
    </>
  )
}
```

