TITLE: Implementing JWT Verification in authDecoder using jose
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the complete implementation of the `authDecoder` function. It imports `jwtVerify` from 'jose', retrieves the Nhost JWT secret from environment variables (encoding it using `TextEncoder`), and then uses `jwtVerify` to asynchronously verify and decode the provided token against the secret. The decoded payload is returned upon successful verification.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/auth/custom.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { jwtVerify } from 'jose'

export const authDecoder = async (token: string, type: string) => {
  if (type !== 'custom-auth') {
    return null
  }

  const secret = new TextEncoder().encode(process.env.NHOST_JWT_SECRET)

  const decoded = await jwtVerify(token, secret)

  return decoded
}
```

