TITLE: Updating Post with Explicit Ownership Verification using Service Function (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a revised approach for updating a post. It first calls the `adminPost` service function (asynchronously) to retrieve the post, implicitly verifying ownership based on `context.currentUser.id` within `adminPost`. If the post is found (meaning the user owns it), it proceeds with the Prisma `update` using only the `id`. Otherwise, it throws a `ForbiddenError`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/tutorial/chapter7/api-side-currentuser.md#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```javascript title="api/src/services/adminPosts/adminPosts.js"
// highlight-next-line
import { ForbiddenError } from '@redwoodjs/graphql-server'

// highlight-start
export const updatePost = async ({ id, input }) => {
  if (await adminPost({ id })) {
    return db.post.update({
      data: input,
      where: { id },
    })
  } else {
    throw new ForbiddenError("You don't have access to this post")
  }
  // highlight-end
}
```
