DESCRIPTION: The `getUser` asynchronous helper function receives the provider user details, access token, and scope. It calls `findOrCreateUser` to get the local user and identity records. Regardless of whether the user was found or created, it updates the corresponding identity record with the latest access token, scope, and sets the `lastLoginAt` timestamp using `db.identity.update`. Finally, it returns the user object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/04_how-to/oauth.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const getUser = async ({ providerUser, accessToken, scope }) => {
  const { user, identity } = await getOrCreateUser(providerUser)

  await db.identity.update({
    where: { id: identity.id },
    data: { accessToken, scope, lastLoginAt: new Date() },
  })

  return user
}
```

