TITLE: Updating a User with $self Skipping Self Uniqueness Conflict in JavaScript/JSX
DESCRIPTION: Handles user updates by ensuring the unique fields (like email) ignore the current record during uniqueness checks using $self. Without $self, an update would falsely fail if the record already exists. The validateUniqueness call receives the id in $self to bypass the user's own record. Requires validateUniqueness() and db.user.create().
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/services.md#_snippet_56

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
const updateUser = (id, input) => {
  return validateUniqueness('user', {
    email: input.email,
    $self: { id }
  }, (db) => db.user.create({ data: input })
}

```

