TITLE: Testing Article Component Rendering and Summary in TypeScript (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript test suite uses `@redwoodjs/testing` (`render`, `screen`) to verify the rendering behavior of the `Article` component. It defines a constant `ARTICLE` containing sample blog post data. The first test case (`renders a blog post`) checks if the component renders the full article title and body when no `summary` prop is provided. The second test case (`renders a summary of a blog post`) asserts that the component renders the title and a specific truncated version of the body when the `summary={true}` prop is passed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/tutorial/chapter5/first-test.md#_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: jsx
