TITLE: Applying Redwood Directives to GraphQL Query and Type Field (Masking)
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL SDL snippet demonstrates combining directives in RedwoodJS. The `@requireAuth` directive on the `user` query ensures only logged-in users can execute it. The custom `@maskedEmail(role: "ADMIN")` directive on the `email` field within the `User` type transforms the email value (e.g., masks it) unless the authenticated user has the 'ADMIN' role.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/directives.md#_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
  type User {
    id: Int!
    name: String!
    email: String! @maskedEmail(role: "ADMIN")
    createdAt: DateTime!
  }

  type Query {
    user(id: Int!): User @requireAuth
  }
```

