TITLE: Implementing a RedwoodJS Transformer Directive (`@maskedEmail`) (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Provides the JavaScript implementation for the `@maskedEmail` transformer directive using `createTransformerDirective` from `@redwoodjs/graphql-server`. It defines a `transform` function that takes the `resolvedValue` (the original field value) and replaces all alphanumeric characters with asterisks ('*'), effectively masking the data. This implementation does not use the `permittedRoles` argument shown in its schema definition.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/directives.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { createTransformerDirective, TransformerDirectiveFunc } from '@redwoodjs/graphql-server'

export const schema = gql`
  directive @maskedEmail(permittedRoles: [String]) on FIELD_DEFINITION
`

const transform: TransformerDirectiveFunc = ({ context, resolvedValue }) => {
  return resolvedValue.replace(/[a-zA-Z0-9]/i, '*')
}

const maskedEmail = createTransformerDirective(schema, transform)

export default maskedEmail
```

