TITLE: Using the toHaveCached Matcher in RedwoodJS Tests (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the three primary ways to use the `toHaveCached` Jest matcher in a RedwoodJS test scenario. It shows checking for data existence regardless of key, checking for data at a specific key, and checking for data in a key matching a regular expression.
