TITLE: Initializing Memcached Client and Service Cache in RedwoodJS - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the initialization of a Memcached client and integration with RedwoodJS's built-in cache utilities. The snippet sets up custom logging, connects to a Memcached server, configures error handling, and exports the `cache` and `cacheFindMany` utility functions. Key dependencies include `@redwoodjs/api/cache` and a Redwood project logger. Environmental configuration can be applied for server address flexibility.
