TITLE: Updating Function to Throw Error on Incorrect Argument Count in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the modified `add` function, updated to meet the requirements of the error test. It uses the rest parameter syntax (`...nums`) to capture all arguments into an array. It then checks if the length of the `nums` array is exactly 2. If not, it explicitly throws the error message 'add() requires two arguments'. Otherwise, it proceeds to return the sum of the first two arguments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emelleby/docwood/blob/main/docs/content/03_reference/docs/testing.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
const add = (...nums) => {
  if (nums.length !== 2) {
    throw 'add() requires two arguments'
  }
  return nums[0] + nums[1]
}
```

